name: Google IO 17 Extended GDG AAUA
description:
Google I/O is an annual software developer-focused conference held by Google in San Francisco, California. Google I/O features highly technical, in-depth sessions focused on building web, mobile, and enterprise applications with Google and open web technologies such as Android, Chrome, Chrome OS, Google APIs, Google Web Toolkit, App Engine, and more.

In this event we plan to make further usefulness of the knowledge in android to develop a stabilized app to wrap up the udacity course and also dive into effective use of google APIs.

Target Audience:

All are welcome to join, but the event will major on intermediate developers and above.

The event is targeted for all developers, students, designers, developers, both men and women, who have acquire skills in html and html5 and android, and then expose them on how to make effective use of them

name: DevFest 2017 AAUA

This Event will also welcome GDG Ado-Ekiti, GDG Akure, GDG Eksu, GDG Benin

name: Cloud Study Jam '18 GDG AAUA
description:
Study Jams are community-run study groups for students on Google Developers content, on various product topics.
The objective of Study Jams is to raise the technical proficiency of our global community members through the highest possible course completion rate.

Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin?
Join us for our Cloud Study Jam! Together we'll work through three Google Cloud Platform Essentials labs, then you will get free access to the next quest so you can finish this series of labs at home to get a Google-hosted badge for your online profile. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Docker, Kubernetes and Scientific Data Processing, which will earn you additional badges.
Join this meetup to get official Google training, a $70+ value, free of charge.
Bring a laptop (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed.
Finally, Get Google-hosted badges for their online profiles, to show potential employers what they know about Cloud computing

name: Web Mobile Study Jam '18 GDG AAUA
description:
Why do I need great mobile web skills?

Mobile now accounts for over half of all web traffic. Users expect their small-screen experiences to be as quick and intuitive as those on desktop. But making the mobile web fast and easy takes some special skills.

53% of mobile visitors will leave if a page takes more than three seconds to load. The average page takes 22 seconds to load, so collectively we're losing a lot of mobile users and giving them a bad experience along the way. Speed is only one part of the picture when creating great mobile experiences.

JOIN US NOW AND BE SKILLED IN MOBILE WEB

name: Build Actions for Your Community: GDG Akoko
description:
• What we'll do
Actions on Google and Google Assistant are one of the major Google technical areas and we want to invite the whole developer community to learn about creating Actions for the Google Assistant.
“Build Actions for Your Community” is an open and modular event series designed by Google and offered to community organizers worldwide.
These are opportunities to developers attending to learn how to build Actions for the Google Assistant that are useful for their community - whether it's a professional network, interest group, or your hometown. This way, you can build something in an area that they care about or are interested in.

• What to bring
Laptop

• Important to know
You’ll learn a lot about the Assistant yourself!
Community members are attracted to new and hot technologies and the series is aimed at all levels of developers - so you’ll be able to get the attention of a broad audience.

name: Flutter Study Jam
description:
Flutter Study Jams are Community-run study groups based on the Flutter Udacity Course. Participants learn how to use Flutter to develop high-quality, interactive mobile applications for iOS and Android devices.

Flutter Study Jam is suited best for: 1) those just getting started with mobile app development 2) those with programming experience on other mobile app frameworks.

name: Google Cloud Next '18 Extended - GDGAKOKO
description:
Join us for this year's Next Extended event, where we'll bring together cloud enthusiasts and the developer community to be a part of the Next '18 experience.

This year, we will be diving deep into cloud with technical keynotes, a hands-on TOPIC (Kubernetes, ML, or Google Cloud Certification) lab, and local speakers.

As an attendee, you'll not only be a part of our vibrant cloud community but also receive free access to Qwiklabs (a $55+ value)!

Don't forget to bring a laptop (PC, Mac, or Chromebook), and get ready for the best Next Extended yet!

Make sure to RSVP to receive upcoming information about this event, and visit https://cloudnext.withgoogle.com/ to learn more about Google Cloud Next '18.
